251
00:21:19,300 --> 00:21:20,990
Is the baby all right?

252
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:31,290
I lost it a few days after the wedding.

253
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:40,690
You're the first person I've told.

254
00:21:44,500 --> 00:21:46,090
I'm so sorry.

255
00:21:48,700 --> 00:21:50,790
I feel like I've lost so much...

256
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:56,090
...that having this baby would change things,but...

257
00:21:58,200 --> 00:21:59,690
now that it's gone...

258
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:05,990
...this isn't the life that I wanted.

259
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:12,990
Does this have anything to do
with what happened the day of your wedding?

260
00:22:19,600 --> 00:22:23,090
You told me you weren't gonna marry lex,
and then, all of a sudden,somehow...

261
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:26,790
something changed your mind.What was it?

262
00:22:29,900 --> 00:22:32,290
It was just wedding-day jitters,that's all.

263
00:22:33,100 --> 00:22:34,490
Lana...

264
00:22:36,600 --> 00:22:38,890
it was more than that.

265
00:22:41,100 --> 00:22:42,690
I can help you.

266
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:45,090
You don't need to be afraid.Whatever you need --

267
00:22:45,100 --> 00:22:48,590
clark, I need you to stop worrying about me.

268
00:22:50,100 --> 00:22:51,690
It's okay, really.

269
00:22:54,700 --> 00:22:58,290
I'm going to get through this
like I always do.

270
00:23:12,300 --> 00:23:15,290
When my wife ends up in the hospital,
that means you've made a grave mistake.

271
00:23:15,300 --> 00:23:17,690
I didn't mean for anyone else to get hurt.

272
00:23:17,700 --> 00:23:19,490
I just wanted you to suffer.

273
00:23:22,700 --> 00:23:25,890
Well, clearly chloe gets her brazenness
from her mother's side.

274
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:30,390
But as meddlesome as she can be,
I've actually come to admire her.

275
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:33,790
That's what makes this so difficult.

276
00:23:33,800 --> 00:23:36,190
You stay away from my daughter.

277
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:38,490
Oh, it's too late for that.

278
00:23:47,900 --> 00:23:49,390
Clark?

279
00:23:50,900 --> 00:23:52,190
Clark?

280
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:55,390
Clark?

281
00:23:55,900 --> 00:23:58,990
- Hey. How's lana?
- She's okay.

282
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:00,490
What'd you find out?

283
00:24:00,800 --> 00:24:05,490
My mom was playing simon says with that guy
at the mansion,which means she's desperate.

284
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:06,890
He told mewhere I could find her.

285
00:24:06,900 --> 00:24:07,990
Can we trust him?

286
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:10,690
Well, there is an old, abandoned hospital
on paper mill road,

287
00:24:10,700 --> 00:24:12,690
just like he said,and it's owned by --

288
00:24:12,700 --> 00:24:13,990
luthorcorp.

289
00:24:14,000 --> 00:24:16,290
It's probably another 33.1 franchise.

290
00:24:16,300 --> 00:24:17,490
I was gonna go check it out,

291
00:24:17,500 --> 00:24:20,590
but I thought it would be more wise
for me to come get my army of one.

292
00:24:26,500 --> 00:24:31,890
Chloe, get out of smallville, sweetheart,
as fast as you can.

293
00:24:34,900 --> 00:24:36,990
- Where you going?
- I have to leave.

294
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:38,890
- Chloe --
- let me go, clark.

295
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:40,690
I have to leave town.

296
00:24:41,100 --> 00:24:42,990
I'm not letting you go anywhere.

297
00:24:46,100 --> 00:24:46,790
What's going on?

298
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:48,590
It's your mom trying to control you again.

299
00:24:48,600 --> 00:24:50,590
Oh, my god.

300
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:51,990
Are you okay?

301
00:24:52,600 --> 00:24:53,890
Yeah, I'm just dizzy.

302
00:24:55,400 --> 00:24:58,290
- Can you get me a glass of water?
- Yeah.

303
00:25:11,900 --> 00:25:14,690
Sorry, clark,but I have no choice.

304
00:25:14,700 --> 00:25:16,790
Please...don't do this.

305
00:25:19,600 --> 00:25:21,790
It's the only way I'll be able
to get out of smallville.

306
00:25:53,900 --> 00:25:54,790
STOP

307
00:25:58,000 --> 00:25:59,590
- I need to get through.
- Sorry, miss.

308
00:26:00,700 --> 00:26:04,190
No.You don't understand.
I need to leave town right now.

309
00:26:04,300 --> 00:26:06,290
I'm afraid we're gonna have to reroute you.

310
00:26:06,500 --> 00:26:07,890
What are you --

311
00:26:24,600 --> 00:26:26,190
Mom?

312
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:34,090
Mom!

313
00:26:38,100 --> 00:26:39,190
Chloe.

314
00:26:46,600 --> 00:26:49,490
You're even more beautiful than I remember.

315
00:26:49,800 --> 00:26:52,290
I can't believe you're awake
and you're talking.

316
00:26:52,800 --> 00:26:54,890
I thought I'd never
get to speak to you again.

317
00:26:55,400 --> 00:26:57,290
Honey,you shouldn't be here.

318
00:26:58,000 --> 00:26:59,990
This is all my fault.

319
00:27:00,000 --> 00:27:01,290
No, it's not.

320
00:27:01,300 --> 00:27:03,990
You needed my help.

321
00:27:05,200 --> 00:27:08,990
You're suffering because of what I made you do,

322
00:27:09,200 --> 00:27:10,790
just like when you were little.

323
00:27:10,800 --> 00:27:11,990
What?

324
00:27:14,900 --> 00:27:18,890
Remember when you were 8
and you hurt your hands?

325
00:27:19,200 --> 00:27:21,190
Yeah, how could I forget?

326
00:27:21,200 --> 00:27:23,390
I had to wear those bandages for weeks.

327
00:27:23,400 --> 00:27:25,590
You know, I've never
played kickball since then.

328
00:27:26,100 --> 00:27:28,290
You didn't hurt your hand playing kickball.

329
00:27:33,800 --> 00:27:36,490
You came home from school,

330
00:27:37,100 --> 00:27:39,590
and your hands were all covered in ink.

331
00:27:40,000 --> 00:27:44,090
So, I told you to go wash your hands,
and instead, you --

332
00:27:45,100 --> 00:27:47,290
you went to play with your computer.

333
00:27:48,600 --> 00:27:50,590
I was so frustrated.

334
00:27:52,600 --> 00:27:56,590
I sent you to go wash your hands

335
00:27:56,600 --> 00:27:59,990
and scrub them till all the ink was gone.

336
00:28:03,100 --> 00:28:04,290
Mom, what are you saying?

337
00:28:04,800 --> 00:28:08,390
I found you in the bathroom.

338
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:10,890
There was blood everywhere.

339
00:28:10,900 --> 00:28:13,190
You had scrubbed your hands raw.

340
00:28:14,600 --> 00:28:16,590
That's why I left --

341
00:28:16,900 --> 00:28:18,790
to protect you from me.

342
00:28:22,800 --> 00:28:25,690
And now I have to protect you from lex luthor.

343
00:28:27,500 --> 00:28:29,190
This man that brought you here --

344
00:28:29,200 --> 00:28:30,990
he knows you're infected.

345
00:28:31,600 --> 00:28:33,190
You have to get out of here.

346
00:28:33,500 --> 00:28:35,590
No. We have to get out of here.

347
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:38,190
Mom, you can control people with powers.

348
00:28:38,200 --> 00:28:40,690
Is there anyone in here
whose ability could free us?

349
00:28:46,700 --> 00:28:48,190
I'd love to.

350
00:28:48,800 --> 00:28:50,990
Yes, lunch before the meeting is perfect.

351
00:28:51,300 --> 00:28:52,490
Okay. Bye-bye.

352
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:56,190
Clark!

353
00:29:02,200 --> 00:29:03,990
Sweetie, wake up!

354
00:29:04,200 --> 00:29:06,290
Clark!

355
00:29:07,200 --> 00:29:09,190
- Mom?
- Oh, baby.

356
00:29:16,600 --> 00:29:17,890
No more experiments.

357
00:29:17,900 --> 00:29:18,790
Keep walking.

358
00:29:20,100 --> 00:29:23,190
Help! I need help in here, please! Help!

359
00:29:26,400 --> 00:29:27,990
My mom -- she's sick.She needs a doctor.

360
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:28,600
What's wrong?

361
00:29:28,610 --> 00:29:30,290
I don't know,but you have to help her.

362
00:29:31,600 --> 00:29:33,690
Hey! Hey!What the hell?

363
00:29:33,700 --> 00:29:35,490
Mom! Mom!

364
00:29:40,400 --> 00:29:43,390
Protect me and my daughter.Set us free.

365
00:29:50,500 --> 00:29:51,590
Stop!

366
00:29:57,200 --> 00:29:58,590
Hold it right there.

367
00:30:10,200 --> 00:30:11,190
Mom!

368
00:30:11,200 --> 00:30:12,390
Chloe!

369
00:30:12,700 --> 00:30:14,090
Go! Get out of here!

370
00:30:15,400 --> 00:30:16,890
Take her back to the cell.

371
00:30:19,500 --> 00:30:23,590
Chloe, whatever you have to do,get out now.

372
00:30:41,300 --> 00:30:42,590
Lex, get out of my way.

373
00:30:43,500 --> 00:30:45,190
I'm sorry.I can't do that.

374
00:30:51,700 --> 00:30:54,090
Don't let your mother make you
do something you'll later --

375
00:31:28,800 --> 00:31:30,890
Hey!I brought sandwiches.

376
00:31:30,900 --> 00:31:34,190
I don't know which ones you like, mom,
so I bought one of each.

377
00:31:34,200 --> 00:31:35,390
I don't think your mom's hungry.

378
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:37,290
Have you talked to oliver?

379
00:31:37,400 --> 00:31:39,890
He said that he would set up a safe place
for her to stay in star city.

380
00:31:39,900 --> 00:31:41,290
Chloe,we have a problem.

381
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:06,490
Mom?

382
00:32:09,500 --> 00:32:10,990
Mom?

383
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:15,390
I-I wanted to see a blue sky...

384
00:32:16,800 --> 00:32:17,990
one last time.

385
00:32:19,800 --> 00:32:21,990
Well, there will be plenty of blue skies
where you're going, mom.

386
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:24,090
You're not gonna be locked inside anymore.

387
00:32:25,300 --> 00:32:26,690
Sweetheart...

388
00:32:28,400 --> 00:32:30,890
...I'm slipping back.

389
00:32:31,900 --> 00:32:35,190
The drug that lex used on your mom --
it only lasts 24 hours,

390
00:32:35,800 --> 00:32:37,490
or else she won't stay lucid.

391
00:32:38,900 --> 00:32:40,890
Chloe, she doesn't have much time left.

392
00:32:41,700 --> 00:32:43,390
Well, I'll go talk to lex.
I'll make a deal with him.

393
00:32:43,400 --> 00:32:47,590
No.No deals with that man.

394
00:32:47,600 --> 00:32:48,790
I can't allow it.

395
00:32:48,800 --> 00:32:50,790
Mom, I already lost you once.
I'm not gonna do it again.

396
00:32:50,800 --> 00:32:54,290
If this drug is out there,
I can get it, trust me.

397
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:57,890
I have some pretty amazing
resources at my disposal.

398
00:33:03,100 --> 00:33:06,290
Being with you again.

399
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:13,790
...It's the greatest gift
I could have ever been given.

400
00:33:16,700 --> 00:33:18,490
But I'm dangerous, chloe.

401
00:33:18,500 --> 00:33:20,590
No, mom.That's not true.

402
00:33:21,700 --> 00:33:26,290
My ability to control people with powers,

403
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:30,690
it's like I'm a human weapon.

404
00:33:30,900 --> 00:33:34,190
And I-I can't --I can't allow it.

405
00:33:34,200 --> 00:33:36,690
But, mom, it doesn't have to be like this.

406
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:44,790
My little cub reporter.

407
00:33:47,800 --> 00:33:49,290
This...

408
00:33:50,100 --> 00:33:51,790
this belongs...

409
00:33:53,800 --> 00:33:55,590
...to you.

410
00:33:55,900 --> 00:33:57,590
No, mom. Please.

411
00:33:59,500 --> 00:34:01,290
Please don't go, mom --

412
00:34:01,600 --> 00:34:04,190
not yet, not again.

413
00:34:14,900 --> 00:34:16,290
I...

414
00:34:18,500 --> 00:34:20,090
...love you...

415
00:34:23,400 --> 00:34:25,790
...chlo-- chloe.

416
00:34:35,400 --> 00:34:37,390
I love you, too, mom.

417
00:35:10,500 --> 00:35:13,290
"Luthorcorp crimesagainst humanity."

418
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:16,090
That's catchy.

419
00:35:19,100 --> 00:35:21,090
Too bad it'll never make it to print.

420
00:35:23,900 --> 00:35:28,590
Lex, I'm tired of playing hardball
or softball or any ball,for that matter.

421
00:35:29,400 --> 00:35:30,490
Game's over.

422
00:35:33,400 --> 00:35:35,690
I'll tell you, your audacity's impressive, chloe,

423
00:35:36,600 --> 00:35:39,390
especially given your recent late-night activities.

424
00:35:42,700 --> 00:35:43,990
What?

425
00:35:44,300 --> 00:35:45,790
You don't remember?

426
00:35:46,900 --> 00:35:49,290
You ran my car off the road a few nights ago.

427
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:51,590
Investigators have boot prints,

428
00:35:51,600 --> 00:35:54,890
hair fibers,samples of the mud found
in your apartment.

429
00:35:54,900 --> 00:35:55,790
***

430
00:35:55,800 --> 00:35:58,890
How many years do you get for
aggravated assault -- 10, 20?

431
00:35:58,900 --> 00:36:00,590
For what you've done, they're
gonna throw away the key.

432
00:36:00,600 --> 00:36:01,690
What I've done?

433
00:36:03,800 --> 00:36:06,990
You don't have a shred of proof
about any of this,and you never will.

434
00:36:08,100 --> 00:36:10,090
But rest assured,

435
00:36:10,400 --> 00:36:13,390
the evidence I have against
you is locked away safe and secure.

436
00:36:16,700 --> 00:36:19,190
Make that article disappear,

437
00:36:19,400 --> 00:36:20,990
and you'll remain a free woman.

438
00:36:22,500 --> 00:36:23,890
Deal?

439
00:36:26,600 --> 00:36:31,690
My mother sacrificed everything
to protect the world from scum like you.

440
00:36:32,100 --> 00:36:36,790
And if taking you down means spending some
quality time behind bars,sign me up.

441
00:36:37,900 --> 00:36:39,590
You know, I thought you might say that.

442
00:36:40,800 --> 00:36:43,290
That's why there's a plan "b"
firmly in place...

443
00:36:46,300 --> 00:36:49,090
...a plan that makes prison
look like a picnic.

